children.subject: This is either a very double or a very difficult schedule depending on many factors including the professors and your mathematical maturity. If you are not a great coder but are decent at math, then you will have plenty of time to focus on 61A (where your grade can be significantly improved by simply practicing over and over again). Also, note that 61A is unlike almost all other programming classes wherein the objective is usually to find some 'trick' rather than to actually use some program architecture for a large programming project. I know many people who consider themselves to be 'bad coders' (i.e. have trouble writing sophisticated programs) but did above average in 61a.
